betterquesting:10.desc:8: The Electromagnetic Separator can get some additional outputs from some ores. Not too important.

This is the first ULV circuit. Make lots.

Glass dust can be made by hammering glass in the crafting table, or by combining Flint and Sand dusts.
No Description
This is the first LV circuit. Batch craft many of these. Eventually, more advanced versions of this first circuit will be possible, making life much easier.

The Large Bronze Boiler is the first machine capable of producing large amounts of steam. It is significantly better than the large bronze boiler.

Use an Endervoir or an Infinite Water Source for power.

The Large Bronze Boiler can run 14 LV steam turbines.
160mb (recipe) * 4 (overclocked to LV) = 640mB

640mB/0.5s (recipe duration) = 640mB/10t = 64mB/t

900mB/t (boiler production) / 64mB/t = 14 turbines

This is the first major crafting component. Prepare to make many.

Follow the lower questline before making the Centrifuge - life will be far easier.

This is the first LV power-producing machine.

One Large Bronze Boiler can power 14 LV Steam Turbines provided you have the fluid transfer rate. 

The cables of choice for LV will be 4x Tin Cables. Insulation makes these cables loose less energy per block. Uninsulated lossy cables will shock you. If you do run 15 LV turbines, you should decentralize your power production. Do batches of 4 LV turbines and transport the steam instead of EU - you will be better off. You really shouldn't need more than 4A for the LV Tier.

Another important component.

Complete the lower quest chain before the upper. Your life will be much easier.
This machine makes plates at a 1:1 ratio.
This machine makes foils for much cheaper.

This machine lets you make Rods at a 1:2 ratio. 2 ingots -> 2 rods + 4 small dust = 1 regular dust, resulting in a net consumption of 1 ingot and production of 2 rods. A better 1:2 ratio without dusts is available at MV.
This macerator only has the first output slot, instead of three shown in JEI. You unlock the second and third at HV. This is the first ore doubling machine.

This machine magnetizes materials without needing redstone. It is required to magnetize steel rods.

In order to power this at first, you will need to use a 4A LV transformer, in transform-up mode. Use a Soft Mallet to swap the modes. This will use 4A of ULV power and turn it into 1A of LV. Use tin or zinc cables at LV.

This machine is the first step in producing Liquid Rubber. Centrifuge the Rubber item into Raw Rubber Pulp, and other materials. You could also use an extractor, but centrifuging also yeilds Glue, which will be useful later. Plus, this machine can be used to process ores further.

Gregtech drums are very useful for fluid storage at this point. They are portable, and can be filled directly from the GUI.

You will build lots and lots of chemical reactors.

More use for drums. Cells act like stackable buckets, which also help. Another great way is with enderIO tanks. Steel and Tungstensteel cells can hold partial fluid quantities (i.e. 576mB).
Another component. It can be used as a cover to import or export fluids, and can also be filtered. Configure it by RClicking with a screwdriver in hand.
It does what it sounds like.
It will help you get more materials from certain ore dusts. Use it to produce antimony for the Battery and Soldering Alloys.
This machine makes alloys. It also makes the Primitive Blast Furnace completely obsolete other than steel at this point.

It puts items into items. 

Battery buffers output the same amount of amps as there are batteries inside them.

Another component.

This can be used as a cover to move items. It supports all the advanced item transfer features.

Another Component

This can also be used as a configurable cover for moving items. It cannot use more advanced item transfer features, like only allowing a certain amount of items in an inventory.
This machine allows you to make all of the components for much cheaper. This machine is a priority for every voltage tier.

You can use this to produce better infinite water sources.

It can also process some ores to get special byproducts. The two fluids that have this ability are Sodium Persulfate and Mercury.

Mica Insulator foil can be used for EBF coils. 

Silicon dioxide is a great source of Silicon. It can be obtained by electrolyzing sand.

This machine combines items that are normally craftable. It can also make early game cables for cheaper, allowing for them to be made with carpet directly, instead of also using string. You really should be using rubber at this point though.
This machine can turn gem dusts into gems, among other things.
The Sifter sifts certain crushed purified ores into gems. Will be important later on.
It blends things together, Will be more useful later on.
It washes ores into clean versions. Needed to sift for gems.

It can recylce many things. 

Additionally, it can create Wrought Iron directly, and make Annealed Copper. It also makes glass at a 1:2 ratio. Oxygen can be produced by electrolyzing water, or centrifuging air. Air is generated with Air Collectors.

Another method of power generation is with Light Fuel and Diesel Generators. 

There is a much better setup available at MV which utilizes Diesel.

Distill oil into sulfuric light fuel, and react it with hydrogen into regular light fuel. Use that in the diesel generator. The LV distillery and LV Diesel generator are re-used for this better setup.
Make 2 Stacks of Cupronickel.
Extracts fluids from items.

These coils will be used in the Electric Blast Furnace. They also have other uses.

In the blast furnace, coil tier dictates what recipes can be run. A recipe that exceeds the temperature of the coils cannot be run in the blast furnace. Higher temperature coils do not speed up the machine, only allowing it to run new recipes. You can speed up the EBF with higher voltage.

The first thing you will make with this machine is Aluminium. Even though the EBF uses MV power, you can power it with 2 LV Energy Hatches for now. As soon as you are able to, replace the two with an MV energy hatch.

It also produces steel, so the Primitive Blast Furnace is now obsolete.

This is the main MV material.

The best cables at MV are Annealed Copper. You could also make MV Superconductor Base cables, but they take more effort. Later tier superconductor bases are much harder. You won't be able to make proper superconductor wires until the end of HV.

This fluid will be used to produce better circuit boards, as well as for special ore processing.

Gallium will be important throughout the game. It is used to make diodes for right now. Gallium Arsenide will yeild more. Arsenic can come from Cobaltite.

These basic diodes will eventually be phased out.
This material can only be made in the Alloy Blast Furnace.
Just like the LV, but made of Aluminium.

This is the first MV circuit. Better circuits will be available soon.

Make the LV Circuit Assembler next.
Same as the LV, but better.
It is used to process ores even further, not super necessary.

This is a general purpose machine, with some exclusive recipes. Very useful.

You can now make rods at a proper 1:2 ratio.
Use Pure Thorium fuel directly into waste.
This is required to produce Ethanol.

This machine can produce various coal products. Namely charcoal and coke. Both are good for fuel. Additionally, Coal Tar, and Wood Vinegar are useful as well. For Ethanol, the chemical being worked towards with these quests, I reccomend producing Wood Vinegar (which also produces charcoal).

Making Wood Tar, and distilling it into Benzene for use in Gas Turbines is also very advisable.

Ethanol can be produced in 4 different ways.

1. Distillation of Wood Vinegar from a Pyrolyse Oven
2. Distillation of Fermented Biomass from a Pyrolyse Oven
3. Distillation of Fermented Biomass, produced using biomass from a Brewery, fermented in a Fermenter.

The fourth is with Fermentation Base.

This isn't required at the moment, but it will be useful later on. Bio diesel is also a good source of power, it is used to make it.
Converts any voltage to any other voltage. Hatches only work parrel to each other, on the horizontal axes.

The Large Forge Hammer is just like the regular forge hammer, except it requires very small amounts of Lubricant.

It requires a Piston Component Block. The tier of the component block is the maximum voltage it can run at.
You will need this for the entire modpack. Make it with Sulfur and Water.

Ethylene is the first major chemical. There are 2 main ways to produce this. 
1. React Sulfuric Acid and Ethanol in a chemical reactor.

2. Distill oil into naphtha or light or heavy fuel (naptha recomended), react the the sulfuric fuel with hydrogen, and steam crack the fuel in a reactor. Distill it into ethylene. The cracker unit is better for cracking fuels, you can make it at HV.

Method #2 is recomended.
Simply add oxygen.
Another circuit component.
The Electronic tier circuit board. Remember that Glue from before?
Better Silicon Boules will become available later on.
This is the key machine in making better circuits.
Builds better circuits. It can also build Primitive LV circuits much easier.
This is the second LV Circuit. It is much more efficient than the primitive alternative. You can use tin instead of soldering alloy.
This is the second MV Circuit.
Yet another circuit component.
Another circuit component.
This is the first HV Circuit.
This is the base HV material.
This is an incredibly important chemical. Make it with Hydrogen and Chlorine.

HV Power Suggestion:
1. 8 Oil->Sulfuric Heavy Fuel LV Distilleries, 12 Oil->Sulfuric Light Fuel LV Distilleries

2. 2 LV Chemical reacotrs for desulfurification, 3 LV electrolyzers for hydrogen

3. 1 MV mixer for diesel

4. Power everything with diesel generators, transform down MV generators for the distilleries.

The above setup produces enough diesel for about 7 HV diesel generators and have fuel gain. It produces barely less than enough to run 8 diesel generators, equivalent to 1 Large Combustion Engine (EV) and 3 HV diesel gens.
The HV macerator lets you get the full output from your ores. It has all three output slots.
Just like the LV, but better.
You'll be making these for the rest of the game. Better materials can yeild more. I reccomend making Polyvinylchloride (PVC) for these sooner than later.
This is the T3 LV Circuit. It is also the final one.
This is the first tier of SMD resistors.

This material is only required at LuV+, but it is a useful replacement for rubber until then. React Methanol with Hydrochloric Acid, then react the dust with sulfur.

Its rings can be used for pumps.

You don't need to make this until much later, but it may make life easier at present.

The brewery machine can brew potions, as seen in the Brewing Stand JEI tab. The potions cannot be put into bottles by any means, so they are useless when made this way. Please use the Potion Brewer from Industrial Foregoing, or the Brewing Stand.
This is the T3 MV Circuit.
Another circuit component.
This machine cools down materials. It is used for producing higher tier materials used in the blast furnace, among other things.
This is the T2 HV Circuit
Lossless wires do not require insulation.
Losses HV power!
This is the T1 EV Circuit.
This is the first tier of SMD diodes.
These are the second tier of EBF coils. Refer back to the Cupronickel Coil quest!
The Large Steel boiler consumes the same amount of fuel as the Bronze Boiler, but produces more steam. It produces 1600mB of steam.

This turbine consumes tons of steam to produce power. It requires exactly 4096mB/t (81920mB/s). The Large Titanium Boiler produces slightly less than enough steam to run the turbine. The best rotor available with titanium is the small ultimet rotor (3776EU/t), due to its durability and efficiency. You might prefer to use Cobalt, Sterling Silver, or Rose Gold. The Large Osmium rotor is the easiest 100% efficient rotor.

The first step in rocket construction. 

The launch pad's size is the max length and width of the rocket.

The first structure tower must be on the same y level as the launch pad. The height of the tower is the max height of the rocket.

Builds your rocket. Place it near the launch pad. Scanning the rocket checks its validity for construction.

It requires FE, which can be obtained using a GTEU Converter.
Guides the rocket. Extremely important.
You'll definitely want more than one tank, and possibly more than one thruster. Rocket builds can vary. What's important is that it will make it to the destination (check the assembler!).

Fueling your rocket.

The Fueling Station also requires FE.

Make sure you fully fuel your rocket and wear your filled space suit. Put the Planet ID Chip in the guidance computer through the rocket's GUI. Then press select destination and pick Luna. Then you can launch.

Notable Ores:
Aluminium
Ilmenite
Requires the moon to first obtain!
Better than the regular boule.

You'll need this to survive the moon.

Gregtech Oxygen works in the charge pad. Add the oxygen tanks to the suit chestplate.

Better oxygen tanks unlock later.
It lets you make plastic circuit boards at a better rate. Useful material in general.
No Description
Polytetrafluoroethylene (PTFE) is also known as Teflon. It is important for the creation of Lareg Chemical Reactors, which you will build high quanities of.

This machine is a better version of the chemical reactor. One of its benefits is that it can process multiple different recipes much easier. 

A good example of this is when doing the oil process (next thing). You can have one hydrogen input be accessable for all 4 oil distillation products, and process all of them simulaneously. 

It uses a tiered casing, in this case a motor casing. The tier of the motor casing is equivalent to the maximum input voltage.

It is wise to make 3 of them for the immediate oil processing. Make the casings after figuring out the amount of hatches desired.

This generator produces EV power. It consumes a very small amount of lubricant to run. It can consume a slightly greater amount of Oxygen to boost the output. By default it produces 1A of EV, but boosting it produces 3A. There is no downside. In fact, the diesel produced in the reccommended HV diesel setup can power 1.75 of these, and generates enough excess oxygen to boost at least engines.

If you don't want to use these, you can also use the Rocket Engine. I wouldn't reccomend this until later voltages, however.
This machine is very important to the Nuclear Process. It is also used for a few other things. It does not overclock.

This machine lets you get all possible outputs of distillation. The input hatch must be on the bottom layer, centered. The first output hatch cannot be on the same layer as the controller. The height can be varied. Only one output per layer.

Look at the Specialized Chemistry Questline after completing this quest.

This machine smelts furnace recpies in parallel. The coil tier eventually improves the energy efficiency, and also increases the amount of parallel processes. This machine is very, very fast. The pyrolyse oven also works in the same way with better coils.

This machine cracks specific fluids to enable the extracting of more products from it. It functions similar to the multi-smelter with better coils (you generally will not need to go very high tier with this machine). It is more efficient than cracking fluids in the Chemical Reactor, since you get more output from it. Use this machine.

The first step in making Epoxy. 

Acetic acid is very easy to make, just electrolyzed water and some carbon or oxygen and ethylene. Combine it with Calcium and oxygen for calcium acetate soultion. An infinite calcium supply is possible using bones. Centrifuging bone meal or electrolyzing Ink Sacs are both viable ways of obtaining calcium.

Distill or heat the calcium acetate solution for a 1:1 convertion into Acetone.
Phenol can be made from Cumene and Oxygen, or in a Large Chemical Reactor. The LCR recipe skips over Cumene and creates Phenol in fewer steps. Use the LCR shortcuts if they are available!
Epichlorohydrin can be made through Glycerol or Allyl Chloride. It also has an LCR shortcut. Use it.
Can be made using Bisphenol A, or through an LCR shortcut.
Better circuits in the making.
No Description
No Description
This is the final MV circuit. Congrats!
The next HV circuit.
The second EV circuit.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Large Bending and Forming Machine
betterquesting:10.desc:8: This multiblock acts like the Bending Machine and Forming press. Use a screwdriver on the controller to switch between them. This machine also processes in parallel.

This will help with obtaining higher quality gems, which are important for sensors. 

The boost works as follows: The boost multiplied by the base chance of the recipe is the base chance in the large machine. The boost multiplied by the chance per tier of the recipe is the chance per tier in the large machine. This is how the boost works for all large machines.

This multiblock is the best way to store energy. It drains 10% of the cell's VOLTAGE TIER every tick. For example, using HV cells means it drains 10% of 512V (51.2V) per tick, and NOT 10% of the stored energy. The Power Cells must all be the same voltage.

It is very expensive, but definitely worth building. Talonite Requires Nichrome Coils.
The next blast furnace coil tier.
Its the same as the Large Steam Turbine, but with the other gases instead. Using LPG only requires 128mB/s!

This is Step 1 of the Platinum Process.

The Platinum process is complicated and takes up a lot of space. Build dedicated machines for each step.

Sift the Platinum Salt into Refined Platinum Salt, then run it through a blast furnace to get back some Platinum Metallic Powder. Build dedicated blast furnaces for this process. The Large Sifter gets you significantly more out of your platinum this way, since it actually increases the sifting chance to 100%.
React the Recipricated Platinum Dust with Calcium, to produce platinum!

This is the start of the Palladium Process. There are two ways to approach this. Split your palladium metallic powder supply in half, react half with ammonia, and react the Palladium enriched ammonia with the other palladium metallic powder. Or, you can devote all your metallic powder to the palladium enriched ammonia from the platinum process.

The Palladium Salt can be sifted the same as the Platinum Salt, and processed back into Palladium Metallic Powder, without the blast furnace step.
This is the final step in the Palladium Process
This is the beginning of the Rhodium and Residue processes.

Electrolyze the zinc sulfate.

Blast furnace the crude rhodium metal into rhodium salt.

The next steps in the Rhodium process.

Sift the rhodium nitrate in the large sifter into rhodium filter cake.
Rhodium is important for Rhodium Plated Palladium, which is the LuV base material.
This is the first step of the Ruthenium Process.
No Description
You won't need this until LuV, but it doesn't hurt to process it now.
This is the first method of obtaining Iridium. Better methods will be available later, but you should still process it this way too.
Centrifuge the Sludge Residue.
Centrifuge the metallic sludge dust. Iridium is an important material, it will be used more prominantly at later times.
You can now build Field Generators, which unlocks many new machines. You also can build Larger Super/Quantum Tanks and Chests, change your oil processing buffers to them!

The first IV circuit.

While you can technically progress to IV after you finish the tungsten process, you should build the multiblocks that become available to you right now sooner than later. They are lifesavers.
No Description
Use either Scheelite or Tungstate dust, first available from Mars, to make Sodium Tungstate. This is the beginning of the Tungsten Process.
Can also be used to make Tungstensteel, which is the IV base material.
Has some specific use-cases.
Allows for more complicated mixtures.
Does what you think. This machine is incredibly useful.

This machine produces complex chemicals. It also can produce fermentation base, which is the best way to obtain ethanol. 

The blast furnace coils are used to add a speed modifier in addition to regular overclocking.

It also must have all 5 fluid inputs, 3 fluid outputs, 1 item input bus, and 1 item output, else it will not form.

This machine can function as any of the following:
 - Compressor
 - Lathe
 - Polarizer
 - Fermenter
 - Fluid Extractor
 - Extractor
 - Laser Engraver
 - Autoclave
 - Replicator
The next blast furnace coil tier.

This machine functions as an ore washing plant or a chemical bath.

Fill the bottom layer with water, then fill the top layer.

This machine harvests ore veins with a fortune modifier. Note that you won't get the byproducts you would get through pulverization. Place this machine right above the ore vein, not on the surface. It will make the "scanning" process faster since it starts lower. It takes a while to begin harvesting due to that hidden scanning process. The other large miners use a higher fortune level, and have a higher range. You may prefer to wait and use those instead. You will need all three large miners to build the Void Miner.
As usual.
This machine is extremely useful.
This machine is extremely useful.
This is the last machine that builds circuits §othis §o§r"easily."
Aim for 100% efficiency on carbon fiber. When machines have chanced outputs, they will continue to consume their inputs if the output is full. Be careful!
Glass Fiber is much easier than Carbon Fibers.
The final HV circuit!
No Description
The 3rd EV Circuit.
The 2nd IV circuit.
No Description
It can power 15 HV Steam Turbines, and 1 MV. This is not quite enough for the large steam turbine.
Very useful.
Very useful.
The second large miner with a higher range and fortune bonus. Read the description for the Basic Large Miner.
This is a very important material.
The next coil tier.
This machine is incredibly helpful. Future materials might only have fluid recipes from this machine.
The Nuclear reactor can be used in combination with a Hot Coolant Turbine to produce power, and is otherwise used to create new materials.

This massive multiblock can drill fluids from chunks. Use JEI to see the different fluid veins available. You can find what fluid is in a chunk using a solar scanner. It requires an LV solar panel on top of it, and a data stick as input. Data sticks are reusable.
This machine uses explosives to turn dusts into gems, but also has other uses.
This reactor is better for producing products than producing power.
Every nuclear material goes through this exact process.
Every nuclear material goes through this process. You need to use the Gas Centrifuge.
The 1st LuV circuit.

This machine lets any singleblock machine run up to 16x in parallel. Insert up to 16 (1 machine = 1 parallel, 2 = 2, etc.) single block machines (ONLY ONE TYPE) into an input bus. Add an appropriate energy hatch (16 EV machines = 16A EV). Then use the multiblock like normal.
This is the base LuV material. The hot ingot has a fluid solidifier recipe.

This machine is used to create all future components. It can be built shorter than max length, but you should definitely build it fully from the beginning. It is difficult to automate. Super Factory Manager or PackagedAuto is a good tool to use to automate recipes for it.

Tip: Recipes that call for multiple of an item in different but consecutive slots can actually have all of that item in one slot, and the next item type in the slot directly after the combined slot.

It must have ULV input buses, and any output bus.

Note that it can make all existing components in large batches for less materials.
This machine is 3x as fast as a blast furnace. It consumes 40mB of Pyrotheum per second while running. It cannot run at all without pyrotheum. This machine is entirely worth making.
You might notice that you need a saw to make wooden planks, and that crafting tables are made of logs. Make sticks with saplings for now.

GregTech tools don't have an entry in JEI. Look for the darmstadtium tools, and they will show all the recipes for the different materials. 

It is recommended to make a black sheep pen for black wool.

These tools are essential to the early game. They will be used to craft many items and components. With machines, these tools become obsolete. 

The yeild of ores can also be increased with these tools, so don't smelt all of it quite yet! Break ores with the hammer to get crushed ores, craft the crushed ones with a hammer to make impure dust. Smelt the dust into ingots! You can throw the impure dust into a filled cauldron for pure dust. Pure dust won't get you anything extra at this stage (needed to get redstone from impure though!).

Make these tools out of iron, and in the Steam Age, out of wrought iron or bronze. Afterwards, choose what you like!

The shears will be required at some point (don't hurt sheep!). All quests, excluding the Iron Hammer and Shears, accept any material for the tool. You don't have to make them all right away, so you can save your iron for wrought tools (more durability).

There are other tools also available to craft, but these are the most important. You can find them in JEI by searching §7§e§e§e§e&meta_tool§f.
This block makes crafting recipes with tools much easier. It can also view attached inventories.
This machine is extremely powerful.

This is the first machine you will make. You may want many. It is used to produce Wrought Iron, Steel, Red Alloy, and more. This quest asks for the exact amount of materials used in 1 PBF.

The Wooden Form is not consumed when used in crafting. Clay can be made with a mortar, and Brick dust can be made with a hard hammer.

Important crafting component. Will be easier at LV.

Sticky resin can be obtained from smelting plantballs, which can be obtained by compressing leaves or other organic materials. 

It will eventually be replaced with SMD components.

Important crafting component. Will be easier at LV.

Sticky resin can be obtained from smelting plantballs, which can be obtained by compressing leaves or other organic materials.

Greenhouses grows crops. NuclearCraft Infinite Water sources are very helpful, and much faster than the EnderIO Endervoir.

Grow something that can be turned into Fermentation Base or Biomass.
The first step in the Gold Processing chain.
No Description
The final step in the gold processing chain.
Nitric acid is used to begin the gold process. Look in the Specialized Chemistry Questline for details.

You will be producing far more U238, but it cannon be processed by itself. Use the U235 in Oxide form in conjunction with Pure U238 (circuits 1-9). After thermal centrifuging the nuclear waste, run the neptunium through the nuclear material processes.

Use the Np237 in oxide form to directly process it in another nuclear reactor (circuits 11-19). Use the Plutonium gained from neptunium waste.

The following is the main route to Plutonium 244, an important material for the next circuit tiers. You will also be able to create Pu244 through Naquadria or fusion later on.

When it comes to making nuclear products, it is best to use the most common isotope wherever possible: U238, Np237, Pu244, Am243, Cm250, Bk249, Cf252, Es255, Fm258, and Md261.
Process Plutonium and run it through the nuclear process to make Pu244, and processing the depleted fuel.
You will still need to build regular assemblers! Tiered components require the same tier of singleblock, so running this at LuV requires an LuV Assembler.
This is what you needed the Pu244 primarily for.
An important component for all future circuits.

This machine is required for making all future circuits. The voltage is tied to the Integral Framework tier. You can use IV or LuV Frameworks, but note that the LuVs are gated behind Incoloy MA-956 and the Naquadah process.
The Final EV Circuit. Circuits will start to become more complicated post Quantum.
Not much harder than Epoxy Circuit Boards. Future boards get much more complicated.
No Description
No Description

Americium can be reached in 2 ways. The first is reacting Pure Pu244 Fuel with various other fuels in a regular reactor. The second is to process U238 Oxide and 235 Pure in  a breeder reactor, instead of a regular, in order to produce depleted Pu239 for processing.
The 3rd IV circuit.
No Description
There are two ways to produce graphene. The better route is through Graphene Oxide.
These are used in later circuits, and high tier transformers.
The 2nd LuV circuit.
This material will be important to progression after making the Fusion Reactor. Make it from Heavy Metal Waste.
No Description
No Description
Starting with these, some circuits will be made in the Assembly Line. This is the first ZPM circuit.
No Description
Even better large miner. All future miners will be Void Miners, but are more complicated to automate.
One of three High Speed Steels. It will be important at ZPM.

Note: Naquadah and Enriched Naquadah have centrifuging recipes to make Naquadria. Naquadria can be Large Centrifuged into many useful materials, like Lutetium and Pu244.

Naquadah Reactors are great sources of power. Note the complex fuel process, and the useful products made from Complicated Naquadah Gas and Enriched Naquadah Solution. Naquadah Gas is also a very good fuel source for Gas power.
No Description
These are a massive jump for circuit production.
No Description
This is the gate for LuV Integral Frameworks.

This is a Parallel Vacuum Freezer. It requires Cryotheum, at the same rate as the Volcanus requires Pyrotheum. 

This machine is highly reccomended.
This generator can make huge amounts of power. It consumes fuel as fast as provided, so make sure to regulate the input.

This machine will fuse two liquids into another. When using 16 LuV energy hatches, the maximum energy to start is 1.6M EU. Fluid inputs can be placed on the bottom and top rows of 3 casings. Fluid outputs can be placed on the middle rows of 3 casings. Energy hatches are placed in the middle row, the corners.

When processing a recipe, it will consume the energy to start initially, then draw the recipe's EUt. 

Plasmas can be used for power using Plasma Generators or eventually the Large Plasma Turbine. The turbine outputs the non-plasma versions of the inputs.

Materials producable in this reactor: Helium Plasma, Platinum, Iron, Potassium Plasma, Europium, Chrome, Oxygen Plasma, Osmium, Lutetium, and Rutherfordium.
This gives access to much cheaper LV and MV circuits.
This gives access to much cheaper HV circuits.
No Description
Rutherfordium is the replacement for standard GT's Europium being the first major fusion material. Rutherfordium is quite important, so make lots.
No Description
Much cheaper EV circuits will be available using these at ZPM.

Use Rutherfordium to make the initial Raw Crystal Chip. EBF it once into an Engraved crystal chip, and cut that into two Raw Chips. Keep repeating to build up a good stock of Engraved, and Engrave those to produce Crystal CPUs.
This is the final IV circuit.
No Description
The third LuV Circuit.
This is the 2nd ZPM circuit.
This is the first UV circuit.

This massive multiblock must be built to the full height. It can run as 12 parallel distilleries, or 4 parallel distillation towers. It must be built to the full height, and every layer must have a fluid output. The casing to the left of the controller must be an item input bus, used for configuration circuits with the distillery mode. The voltage tier is NOT tied to the framework tier, unlike other multiblocks. It requires IV Voltage frameworks when being built.
LuV Tier Framework.
Use Am243 Oxide fuel and deplete it directly.
Used in the Fusion Reactor Mark 2.

The same placement rules as the Mark 1 apply here as well. This reactor has a max energy to start of 320M EU.

It can create: Uranium 238, Radon Plasma, Tungsten, Nitrogen Plasma, Iron Plasma, Americium, Naquadah, Duranium, Tritanium, and Dubnium.

Dubnium is required for later progression, but your first priority is making Tritanium.

This quest chain will detail the production of Sterilized Growth Medium. Good luck!

Mince meat is used to produce Blood and Animal Cells. You will most likely be bottlenecked by blood.
No Description
These will be used mostly later on.
No Description
No Description
Quicklime can be made in a chemical reactor from calcite.
Note the Silver Catalyst.
Note the Copper Catalst.
Remember sticky resin? You can centrifuge Rubber Wood for them.
No Description
